The Idea in One Paragraph
A mobile-first app that replaces the chaos of WhatsApp groups, Discord channels, and "just show up" culture for amateur sports coordination. Instead of text threads where messages get buried, users see upcoming matches as interactive visual football fields — showing exactly who's playing, in what position, and how the lineup is filling up in real time. Everything happens inside Communities (called Squads in some screens): campus groups, city groups, workplace teams, friend groups. The product is built for Morocco first (Casablanca, campus-based launch), Gen-Z and millennial amateur athletes, with football as the anchor sport and basketball/handball as secondary.

Core Concept: How It Works
The user flow is three layers stacked on top of each other:
Layer 1 — Communities (Squads): You join one or more communities. A community is a container. Examples: "The Campus," "Casablanca Sports," "Engineering School," a company's internal group. Communities are either Public (one-tap join) or Private (admin approval required, marked with a red "Private 🔒" badge).
Layer 2 — Matches: Inside each community, members create matches. Matches come in two flavors: Team vs Team (two organized teams face off, shown with a yellow "VS" badge between two lineups) and Random Matches (pickup games where individual players fill slots on a single field).
Layer 3 — The Visual Lineup: This is the hero feature. Every match displays as a football pitch in 3D perspective with player avatars positioned in formation (4-3-3, 4-4-2, etc.). You see who's in, who's pending, and which slots are empty — before committing. You tap "Join Match," the captain approves, your avatar appears on the field.
Secondary features: tournaments, teams (persistent squads within a community), player profiles with feedback scores, invites, and notifications.

Design System
Colors:

Background: Deep black (#000 / near-black) across every screen
Primary accent: Neon yellow-green (approximately #D4FF3A / lime-yellow) — used for the main CTA buttons ("Publish," "Join Match," "Invite Members," "Create Community," "Accept" highlights), the active calendar day, the "+" floating action button, and the "VS" badge between teams
Secondary accent: Subtle green-yellow on labels (Location, Time, Group, Match Format field headers)
Text: White for primary, muted gray for secondary/inactive states
Status colors: Red-tinted badge for "Private," green for "Public," green rating star (4.5 ★)
Emoji reaction colors on feedback: green background bars with emoji icons (😍 Teamwork, 😁 Attitude, 😌 Attendance, 😠 Technical)

Typography: Bold condensed display font for page titles in ALL CAPS ("DISCOVER MATCHES," "MY COMMUNITIES," "MATCH DETAILS," "NOTIFICATIONS") — gives a sports-broadcast, FIFA-adjacent feel. Body text is clean sans-serif.
Component language: Rounded cards (≈16–20px radius) on dark gray fills, pill-shaped toggles and tabs, floating yellow circular "+" button in the bottom-right corner across most screens, bottom tab bar with Home / Community / Profile and the "+" hovering on the right.
Lineup rendering: Football field drawn with white outlines (goals, penalty boxes, center circle), aerial 3D-perspective angle, circular player avatars with the player's first name underneath, empty positions shown as gray placeholder circles with a generic silhouette. A "19/22" counter in yellow shows how full the match is.

