The Visual Lineup — The One Thing That Matters
Almost every screen is a wrapper around the lineup. The core asset is:
A dark football pitch rendered in slight 3D perspective, white field lines (goals top and bottom, center circle, penalty boxes), circular player avatars (real photos, not generic icons) placed in formation positions with the player's first name in white underneath. Empty slots are gray circles with a generic person silhouette. A counter in yellow — "19/22" — shows fill status. For Team vs Team, two half-fields stack vertically with a yellow "VS" badge between them. The lineup appears in miniature on cards in the feed and full-size on match detail, team detail, and share screens. It's the same asset at three sizes, which is smart — it's the product's visual DNA.
